description:
Vertigo's fifth one-shot in a series of anthology titles. All one-shots feature different artists and focus on short stories about science fiction, ghosts, horror, and the weird and unexpected.

"Time Warp" deals with science-fiction and its title is inspired by the DC series from the late 1970s of the same name.

List of Vertigo's themed anthology titles:

  • Strange Adventures
  • The Unexpected
  • Mystery in Space
  • Ghosts
  • Time Warp
  • The Witching Hour
name: Time Warp

description:
Bios/guides to popular Marvel characters.

This series is released weekly and is available in multiple countries in print and digital editions.

Marvel Fact Files is a weekly publication that builds up to create a fantastic in-depth guide to the Marvel Universe, packed with information on all the heroes and villains, their weapons, vehicles and technology.

Every issue features original cutaway artwork that reveals hidden secrets, detailed profiles of characters, a history of the teams, and a timeline of Marvel's greatest battles, plus inside information about the history of Marvel Comics.
name: Marvel Fact Files

description: "Quest 2: The Halls of Anubis!" Written by Scott Behnke. Art by Kent Burles. Anubis, Guardian of the Dead! In this sequel to The Chaos Gate, the Adventurers continue their desperate quest to obtain the five Keys of Telku - the only items powerful enough to save the North from the destructive armies of Accuris and Baal. They have the first key and the second is easily obtained. But the third key is in the possession of Anubis, Guardian of the Dead. Before they can even challenge this powerful foe, they must overcome the horrifying Trials of the dead - a test which none have ever conquered. Even if they somehow survive, the Adventurers must still face betrayal from within their own ranks.
name: Adventurers: The Halls of Anubis: Quest Two

deck: Malibu, 1990 Series Published in English (United States)
description: "Quest 3: The Ways of the Worm!" Written by Scott Behnke. Art by Kent Burles. The Ways of the Worm is the final chapter in The Chaos Gate saga, and it is the city of Liam's darkest hour. The forces of Accuris and Baal are preparing to crush Liam while the Adventurers scramble to gain the final Key of Telku - the only hope to turn the tide of battle. And where Belegard flies, death surely follows...
name: Adventurers: The Ways of the Worm: Quest Three

deck: Reprinting content from Dark Horse Presents #146 and #147.  A transport spaceship is forced to land on an alien planet for repairs.  Waiting for them are Aliens, instigated by a reclusive billionaire to lure in Predators.  Nobody lives - except the maniac billionaire.  The most terrifying thing on this rock is human.
description: This digital publication was originally published in Dark Horse Presents #146 and Dark Horse Presents #147 - Ragnok. It features Aliens (Xenomorphs) and Predators. They are not the center of the story, however. The focus of the story is on the humans who land on the planet to make repairs and the human living on the planet.
